---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const updated = "October 26, 2025"; // keep this current
---

<BaseLayout
    title="Privacy Policy — AHS Ratings"
    description="How AHS Ratings collects, uses, and protects your data."
>
    <section class="container py-10">
        <h1
            class="mb-2 text-3xl font-bold"
            style="font-family: var(--font-display)"
        >
            Privacy Policy
        </h1>
        <p class="text-muted">Last updated: {updated}</p>

        <div class="mt-8 space-y-8">
            <section class="space-y-3">
                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Overview</h2>
                <p class="text-muted">
                    AHS Ratings (“we”, “us”) lets people rate each season of <em
                        >American Horror Story</em
                    > and compare with the community. This policy explains what we
                    collect, how we use it, and the choices you have.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section class="space-y-3">
                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Information we collect</h2>
                <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-6 text-muted">
                    <li>
                        <span class="text-text font-medium">Account data:</span>
                        email address, password (hashed), OAuth identifiers (e.g.,
                        Google), email verification status.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <span class="text-text font-medium">Profile data:</span>
                        username, profile picture (stored in Supabase Storage), display
                        preferences (e.g., theme).
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <span class="text-text font-medium">Ratings data:</span>
                        your per-season ratings and timestamps.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <span class="text-text font-medium">Usage data:</span> basic
                        analytics (aggregated or pseudonymous) such as page views,
                        referrers, and device/browser information.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <span class="text-text font-medium"
                            >Cookies & local storage:</span
                        > session cookies for authentication and a small key for
                        theme preference.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section class="space-y-3">
                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">How we use information</h2>
                <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-6 text-muted">
                    <li>
                        Provide, secure, and maintain the service
                        (authentication, RLS permissions, profile management).
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Render charts (your profile chart; community averages in <code
                            >/stats</code
                        >).
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Improve features and performance (troubleshooting, usage
                        metrics, anti-abuse).
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Communicate with you (account verification, critical
                        updates).
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section class="space-y-3">
                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Sharing & disclosure</h2>
                <p class="text-muted">
                    We don’t sell your personal information. We share limited
                    data with service providers who help us operate the site,
                    strictly for the services they perform:
                </p>
                <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-6 text-muted">
                    <li>
                        <span class="text-text font-medium">Supabase:</span> authentication,
                        Postgres database, Storage/CDN.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <span class="text-text font-medium">Netlify:</span> hosting
                        and serverless functions.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <span class="text-text font-medium"
                            >OAuth providers (e.g., Google):</span
                        > if you choose to sign in with them.
                    </li>
                </ul>
                <p class="text-muted">
                    Public information: your <span class="font-medium text-text"
                        >username</span
                    > and <span class="font-medium text-text">ratings</span> are
                    visible to others (e.g., on your profile and in community feeds/averages).
                    Your email is never displayed publicly.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section class="space-y-3">
                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Data retention</h2>
                <p class="text-muted">
                    We keep account and ratings data while your account remains
                    active. If you delete your account, we will delete or
                    anonymize your personal data within a reasonable period,
                    subject to legal or operational requirements (e.g., backups
                    with limited retention).
                </p>
            </section>

            <section class="space-y-3">
                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Your choices & rights</h2>
                <ul class="list-disc space-y-2 pl-6 text-muted">
                    <li>
                        Update your profile (username and avatar) from your
                        account page.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Modify your ratings at any time from the “Rate” page.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Opt out of theme/local preferences by clearing local
                        storage in your browser.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Request access, correction, export, or deletion of your
                        data by contacting us (see below).
                    </li>
                </ul>
                <p class="text-muted">
                    If you’re in the EEA/UK, you may have additional rights
                    under GDPR, including objecting to certain processing and
                    lodging a complaint with your local supervisory authority.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section class="space-y-3">
                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Security</h2>
                <p class="text-muted">
                    We use Supabase’s managed Postgres with Row Level Security
                    and hashed credentials. No method of transmission or storage
                    is 100% secure; we aim to use reasonable safeguards
                    appropriate to the risk.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section class="space-y-3">
                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">International transfers</h2>
                <p class="text-muted">
                    Our infrastructure and providers may operate in multiple
                    regions. Your information may be processed outside of your
                    country. We rely on our providers’ data transfer mechanisms
                    where applicable.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section class="space-y-3">
                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Children</h2>
                <p class="text-muted">
                    AHS Ratings is not intended for children under 13 (or the
                    minimum age required in your country). We don’t knowingly
                    collect data from children under that age.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section class="space-y-3">
                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Changes to this policy</h2>
                <p class="text-muted">
                    We may update this Privacy Policy. We’ll change the “Last
                    updated” date and, when appropriate, provide additional
                    notice.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section class="space-y-3">
                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Contact</h2>
                <p class="text-muted">
                    Questions or requests? Email us at <a
                        class="underline text-text"
                        href="mailto:support@ahsratings.example"
                        >support@ahsratings.example</a
                    >.
                </p>
            </section>
        </div>
    </section>
</BaseLayout>
